archimate:BusinessObject.name: Legal Interoperability Specification
archimate:BusinessObject.documentation:
Legal interoperability covers the broader environment of laws, policies, procedures and cooperation agreements needed to allow the seamless exchange of information between different organisations, regions and countries.
Legal interoperability specifications support interoperability by addressing the core legal interoperability background for solutions.
Source: How does the EIRA support interoperability? https://joinup.ec.europa.eu/sites/default/files/how_does_eira_support_interoperability_v1_0_0.pdf
